HEADWORD: Monsignore
<hw>Mon`si*gno"re</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Monsignors</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[It.,
my lord. Cf. <er>Monseigneur</er>.]</ety> <def>My lord; -- an
ecclesiastical dignity bestowed by the pope, entitling the bearer to
social and domestic rank at the papal court. (Abbrev.
<abbr>Mgr.</abbr>)</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

